{
  "page": "Rolly Duckfield",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\"><img alt=\"Golden Company.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/50px-Golden_Company.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/75px-Golden_Company.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/100px-Golden_Company.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Rolly Duckfield</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/50px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/75px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/100px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Darek Zabrocki RollyD.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/58/Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg/350px-Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"291\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/58/Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg/525px-Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/58/Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg/700px-Darek_Zabrocki_RollyD.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Rolly, by Darek Zabrocki © Fantasy Flight Games</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Duck<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Ser Duck<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Caswell\" title=\"House Caswell\">House Caswell</a> (formerly)</li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> (formerly)</li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nor before <a href=\"/index.php/280_AC\" title=\"280 AC\">280&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Bitterbridge\" title=\"Bitterbridge\">Bitterbridge</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Rolly Duckfield</b>, also known as <b>Duck</b>, is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> in service to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Young Griff</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Rolly\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Rolly</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Category:Images of Rolly Duckfield\">Images of Rolly Duckfield</a></div>\n<p>Duck is a brawny man. He has a shock of orange hair and a shaggy beard.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Rolly was born in the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>. His father was a <a href=\"/index.php/Blacksmith\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Blacksmith\">blacksmith</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Bitterbridge\" title=\"Bitterbridge\">Bitterbridge</a> in service to old <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Caswell\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord Caswell\">Lord Caswell</a>. Rolly's strength and skill with a blade earned him a place in the castle garrison, but Rolly had dreams of <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighthood</a>. He resented seeing Lord Caswell's weakling son <a href=\"/index.php/Lorent_Caswell\" title=\"Lorent Caswell\">Lorent</a> become a page, a squire, then a knight. Lord Caswell had only one son, so no one in the castle was allowed to say a word against Lorent. In the yard the other squires barely touched him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On his sixteenth name day, Rolly's father made a longsword for Rolly as a present, but Lorent Caswell saw it and claimed it for his own, saying to Rolly that he was only fit to wield a hammer, not a sword. Rolly then fetched a hammer and broke both of Lorent's arms and half his ribs. Afterwards, Rolly quickly fled across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a> to escape Lord Caswell's wrath. He joined the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> as an apprentice smith for a few years, and then served Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harry_Strickland\" title=\"Harry Strickland\">Harry Strickland</a> as a <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Griff</a> needed someone to train his son <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Young Griff</a> in skill at arms, Harry Strickland sent him Rolly. A year later Rolly was knighted by Griff. Having no surname, Rolly chose the name Duckfield because he was in a field with some <a href=\"/index.php/Duck\" title=\"Duck\">ducks</a> when he was knighted, earning him the nickname \"Duck\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/350px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/525px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/700px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rolly kneels before Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, by Mariana Vieira © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Rolly meets <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a>'s litter and escorts <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> to meet the rest of the party. They set sail on the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Shy_Maid\" title=\"Shy Maid\">Shy Maid</a></i> to <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Young Griff is revealed to be <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, and Griff to be <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and they are supported by the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Duck and Jon participate in the <a href=\"/index.php/Landing_of_the_Golden_Company\" title=\"Landing of the Golden Company\">landing of the Golden Company</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>. Duck is named to the new <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> by Aegon, but Jon does not approve of the choice. He thinks Duck is a solid man and true, but not worthy of the Kingsguard, and that they should be reserving positions for famous warriors and younger sons of great lords whose support they will need in the fight for the throne. However, Aegon feels that it is most important that Rolly will die for him, citing the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kingslayer\">Kingslayer</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>, as an example that matches Jon's preferences.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg/350px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"490\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg/525px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e7/Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg/700px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolly_Duckfield_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rolly by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cloudninja9.deviantart.com/\">cloudninja9</a> ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tyrion</b>: Are these two known to you, <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">magister</a>? They look like <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaws</a>. Should I find my axe?<br />\n</p><p><b>Rolly</b>: Your axe? Did you hear that, Haldon? The little man wants to fight with us!<br />\n<b>Haldon</b>: Small men oft feel a need to prove their courage with unseemly boasts. I doubt if he could kill a <a href=\"/index.php/Duck\" title=\"Duck\">duck</a>.<br />\n<b>Tyrion</b>: Fetch the duck.<br />\n<b>Haldon</b>: If you insist.<br />\n<b>Rolly</b>: I'm Duck, you mouthy little pisspot.<br />\n<b>Tyrion</b>: I had a smaller duck in mind.<br />\n<b>Rolly</b>: Did you hear, Haldon? He wants a smaller Duck!<br />\n</p>\n<b>Haldon</b>: I should gladly settle for a quieter one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a>, and Rolly</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Illyrio</b>: How fares <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">our lad</a>?<br />\n</p><p><b>Haldon</b>: He is as tall as <a href=\"/index.php/Griff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Griff\">Griff</a> now. Three days ago he knocked Duck into a <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a> trough.<br />\n<b>Rolly</b>: I wasn't knocked. I fell in just to make him laugh.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Haldon</b>: Your ploy was a success. I laughed myself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a>, and Rolly</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Haldon</b>: Tell <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">our little friend</a> how you came by your name, why don't you?<br />\n<b>Rolly</b>: A <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> needs more than just the one name, and, well, we were in a field when <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">he</a> dubbed me, and I looked up and saw these <a href=\"/index.php/Duck\" title=\"Duck\">ducks</a>, so ... don't laugh, now.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a> and Rolly</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Rolly\">Quotes about Rolly</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Rolly\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png/350px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"332\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png/525px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/4b/Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png/700px-Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolly_Duckfield_by_Bidonicart.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rolly Duckfield, by Bidonicart ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Griff</b>: I am no <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>.<br />\n</p><p><b>Tyrion</b>: And yet Ser Duck says you knighted him.<br />\n<b>Griff</b>: Duck talks too much.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Tyrion</b>: Some might wonder that a duck can talk at all.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Griff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Griff\">Griff</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote> \n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Duck will die for me if need be, and that's all I require in my <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>At least I convinced <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">him</a> to leave the other six slots open, else Duck might have six ducklings trailing after him, each more blindingly adequate than the last.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolly_Duckfield&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.02</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.03</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.04</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.05</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.06</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.07</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.08</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\">1.09</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\">1.10</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\">1.11</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Tyrion III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued3)#Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued3)\">Rolly Duckfield</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cit